The first conjugation is formed by verbs with infinitive ending in ''-à''. There are differences, in present indicative, between monosyllabic and polysyllabic verbs, so we use two examples: ''tirà''="to pull" (polysyllabic) and ''trà''="to throw" (monosyllabic).
